The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Athletes need more support: Bhaichung
                                                                                                                                                                                                       Athletes need more support: Bhaichung
            A STAFF REPORTER            CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya and India captain Bhaichung Bhutia at   a function in Calcutta on Thursday. A Telegraph picture                                 
	Calcutta: Bhaichung Bhutia, the captain of the AFC Challenge Cup winning Indian team, termed Indias performance in the Beijing Olympics as a pleasant surprise and said that the onus now lies with the government and sports authorities to build on the success.         
	Speaking to reporters on the sidelines of a Central Bank of India promotional, Bhaichung said: Our sportsmen have showed that they have it in them to compete successfully on the international stage.         
	The government should now look to develop sports infrastructure.         
	There hasnt been much support from their side to the athletes going into the Olympics, but now that medals have been won the athletes should be rewarded handsomely. Especially the wrestler and the boxer.         
	The striker, who played a leading role in the AFC Challenge Cup triumph, thanked the bank for employing a number of footballers in their ranks. He hoped that the bank would, in its small way, keep doing its bit for football and employ more footballers in the years to come.         
	Jagmohan Dalmiya, the president of the Cricket Association of Bengal, was also present on the occasion.                                                                                                                          
